He saw action in every major battle during Operation Iraqi Freedom using his trusty .300 Win Mag, a bolt-action precision sniper rifle which he said would ‘shoot like a laser’.

Kyle, whose parents are a Sunday school teacher and a church deacon, has said he had no regrets about his life and claimed to have a ‘clear conscience’ before God.

In his memoir he said: ‘It was my duty to shoot the enemy, and I don't regret it.

‘My regrets are for the people I couldn't save: Marines, soldiers, buddies...

